name: ACM Workshop: Intro to Machine Learning
description: Join us for an introductory workshop on machine learning fundamentals. We'll cover basic concepts, algorithms, and hands-on coding exercises using Python and scikit-learn. Perfect for beginners!

name: Fall Cultural Festival
description: Celebrate diversity with performances, food from around the world, and cultural exhibitions. All students welcome to experience the rich tapestry of Princeton's international community.

name: Career Fair: Tech Industry
description: Meet with recruiters from top tech companies including Google, Microsoft, Amazon, and innovative startups. Bring your resume and be ready to network!

name: Thanksgiving Dinner
description: Traditional Thanksgiving feast for students staying on campus. Turkey, stuffing, pumpkin pie, and all the fixings! A great opportunity to celebrate with the Princeton community.

name: Entrepreneurship Panel Discussion
description: Hear from successful Princeton alumni entrepreneurs about their startup journeys, lessons learned, and advice for aspiring founders. Q&A session to follow.

name: Study Break: Finals Prep
description: Take a break from studying with free coffee, snacks, and stress-relief activities. Therapy dogs, meditation corner, and good vibes as we head into finals season.

name: Guest Lecture: Climate Change Policy
host_organization: School of Public and International Affairs
description: Distinguished environmental policy expert discusses the latest developments in international climate agreements and their implications for global sustainability.

name: Winter Concert Series Kickoff
description: The Princeton University Orchestra presents its winter concert featuring works by Beethoven, Tchaikovsky, and contemporary composers. Free admission for students.
